abstract: The author of “Tennessee Williams: Mad Pilgrimage of the Flesh” is not a fan of science fiction. “Life on earth is mysterious and terrifying enough.”

abstract: The Braves stunned Atlanta in November by announcing they would pull up stakes downtown, their home since migrating from Milwaukee in 1966, and move to Cobb County.
snippet: The Braves stunned Atlanta in November by announcing they would pull up stakes downtown, their home since migrating from Milwaukee in 1966, and move to Cobb County.
lead_paragraph: ATLANTA — Beneath a tent erected over a patch of gravel, two dozen nicely dressed dignitaries wearing Atlanta Braves batting helmets plunged custom-made shiny shovels with bat handles into a pit of dirt Tuesday.

abstract: People keep texting when they’re behind the wheel, so an engineer has found a technological solution. The problem: He can’t do it on his own.
snippet: People keep texting when they’re behind the wheel, so an engineer has found a technological solution. The problem: He can’t do it on his own.
lead_paragraph: People know they shouldn’t text and drive. Overwhelmingly, they tell pollsters that doing so is unacceptable and dangerous, and yet they do it anyway. They can’t resist. So safety advocates and public officials have called for a technological solution that does an end run around free will and prevents people from texting in the first place.

abstract: The federal government has provided military-style weaponry to local police departments since the Sept. 11, 2001, attacks, but with little oversight.

abstract: The company says its existing investment arm has set up the Salesforce1 Fund, a $100 million pool of money earmarked for start-ups that can create apps for the Salesforce mobile app platform.
snippet: The company says its existing investment arm has set up the Salesforce1 Fund, a $100 million pool of money earmarked for start-ups that can create apps for the Salesforce mobile app platform.
lead_paragraph: To help make sure that Salesforce.com can compete for the interest of mobile app developers, the corporate software powerhouse is taking an unusual step: setting up a special venture capital fund.
headline_main: Salesforce.com to Set Up a Venture Capital Fund
byline_original: By Michael J. de la Merced

abstract: There is a lot to like about the 2014 Volkswagen Tiguan, but when stacked up against competitors, it may not add up.
snippet: There is a lot to like about the 2014 Volkswagen Tiguan, but when stacked up against competitors, it may not add up.
lead_paragraph: This week in Automobiles, Lawrence Ulrich looks at the 2015 Volkswagen Golfs with the gasoline TSI and diesel TDI engines. The Golf now rides on VW’s new and highly versatile MQB platform, which is expected to be the foundation for 40 different Volkswagen Group products, from Audi to Skoda.

abstract: VW assembled turbo, diesel and even electric-power cars and crossovers in Northern Virginia for journalists to sample.
snippet: VW assembled turbo, diesel and even electric-power cars and crossovers in Northern Virginia for journalists to sample.
lead_paragraph: MIDDLEBURG, Va. — Volkswagen occupied a corner of Northern Virginia’s lush horse country with a collection of its newest vehicles recently, affording a group of journalists a closer look at its 2015 model line. With a chance to sample VW’s wares came an opportunity to reflect on the automaker’s struggle to meet its ambitious sales goals in North America.

abstract: Frank and Ross debate the union of church and real estate in “Love Is Strange” and explore future dystopias in “The Giver.” And one columnists pleads: Stop giving actors extra credit for playing gay.
snippet: Frank and Ross debate the union of church and real estate in “Love Is Strange” and explore future dystopias in “The Giver.” And one columnists pleads: Stop giving actors extra credit for playing gay.
lead_paragraph: Ross Douthat: Now is the Indian summer of our moviegoing discontent, when the temperatures still feel appropriate to midsummer blockbusters but the studios are dumping dreck that would be more at home in the wintry graveyard of late January. (As well as satisfying the millions who were apparently clamoring for a “Forrest Gump” IMAX re-release.) But there are still interesting things to talk about, and I’ll start in with the movie that’s supposed to be the great exception to the current doldrums — “Love Is Strange,” in which John Lithgow and Alfred Molina play longtime companions who tie the knot, only to have Molina’s character lose his job as a music teacher at a Catholic school because the bishop found out about his nuptials, which forces them to sell their tastefully shabby New York apartment and crash (separately, miserably) with their relatives while they try to get on the list for a rent-controlled living situation, with various uncomfortable interpersonal consequences for everyone concerned.

abstract: Since 2008, more than 1,500 people have appeared on five Sunday news and political talk shows: “Meet the Press,” “Face the Nation,” “This Week,” “Fox News Sunday” and “State of the Union.” Many are familiar faces in Washington, where lawmakers, consultants and pundits routinely sound off on the week's news, while others come from the worlds of entertainment and sports. Researchers at American University have collected more than 9,000 appearances. Below is a listing of those guests, excluding network employees or contracted regular guests.
